      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "PALOUSE, April 25.-Palouse\nwill benefit by a great big camp\nmeeting here when the Upper Col\numbia conference of the Seven Day\nAdventists will convene. 1t is ex-\npected that 1000 or more delegates\nwill attend.\n\n\nSTANDPOINT, April 25.-Men who\nmay prove to belong to a gang of\nboxcar thieves have been captured\nhere. A gang has been operating\nhere very extensively and fairly\nsuccessfully.\n\n\nCHENEY. April 25.-That Prin-\ncipal II. c. Sampson of the state\nnormal school may resign, is re-\nport circulating here. 1t is said\nhe will accept an offer with the\nWestern Union Life Insurance com\npany at Spokane.\n\n\nLEWISTON, April PA league\nhas been formed to improve the\ncity streets and general municipal\nconditions. Among the things\nwanted are more cement walks and\nsome parks."
    }
